r.\n[The ceremony was performed at the\nhome of the bride\u2019s parents by the\nRev. S. S. Diehl.\nMrs. Miller, who made her home\nwhile in Trenton with her sister, Mrs.\nEdward F. Grinslade, of 13 Perry\nstreet, is a graduate of the Trenton\nHigh Schol and of Teachers. College,\nColumbia University, where she spe\neialized in home economics. Since\ngraduating from college, she has done\n[educational social work-in the field'\nof Home Economics. For thrde years\nAirs. Miller was assistant secretary.,\nand nutrition_ worker with the As-,\nsociated Charities, Newburgh, N. V,\nand for the past year has been do\ning pioneer,social work for the State\nof Arkansas. i\nTRESPASS NOTICE.\n(:,TMs;^s to notify all persons not to\nhunt ,or trespass in any way what\never on my premises as the law will\npositively be enforced against all tres\npassers,. Mrs. S. M.'Gross.\nWANTED\u2014-Agents for North Ameri\ncan A'cdident Insurance company tc\nsell ;low* cost accident and health\npolicies to men and' women-of any\nv I\nnationality. Liberal com\u00abrission anc\u2019\n_ V,\nexclusive territory to hustlers. Ap\nply to R. M. Laird, Special Agent\nWANTED\u2014Poplar, Ash' and Cypress\nstanding timber.- Will figure with\nyou on any^ si^e-tract. Give full de\ntails in first letter. Hoffman Lum\nber Company, Columbia, S. C.\nUSED Ford Touring Cars, Roadster^,\nfor sale at from $50.00 up. DuPre\nAuto Co.\nFOR SALE OR RENT.5\u2014My place at\nChapin, S. C. Address J. J. Bick\nley, Granite Falls, N. C.\nWANTED\u2014Men or women to take\norders for genuine guaranteed hos\niery for men, women and children;\neliminate gaming. Salary, $75 a\nweek frjll time; $1.50 an hour spare\ntime. Cottons, heathers, silk. In\nternational Stocking Mills, Norris\ntown, Pa.\nFOR SALE\u2014Second-hand two-horse\nwagon cheap for cash. Apply to\nE. J. Sawyer, Lexington, S. C*.\nFOR SALE\u2014Pure Bourbon Red ^and<\nMammoth Bronze turkeys, $10 a>\npair, $14 trio. John Hutto, Lexing\nton, S. C. ltp.\nMrv jVfiU\u00abr is a graduate of Clem*'\nson? College, South Carolina.; He served\ntwo years in the Nary during the\nWorldStar, and is, an active member\nof the American Legion. At present\n\u25a0-be is' connected -with the State Agri\ncultural Extension Service in .South\nCarolina.'\nj Mr. and Mrs. Miller, after spend\ning Some time in New York and\nSouthern Pines, N. C., will reside in\nMcCormick, S. C. v\nCARD OF THANKS.\nj We wish to express through the\ncolumns the Dispatch-News our\nsincere thanks' to the members of\nZion church for the bounteous dona\nj tion made at the parsonage on Christ\nmas eve. When a number of the\nmembers of the church came and left\nso many evidences of love and good\nwill in the form of substantial pro\nvisions for the pantry, the members\nof the other congregations have also\nshown -their appreciation of our\nJwork, and services ahiong them by\nsubstantial gifts in cash and kind\nat this season and throughout the\nentire year. May God\u2019s richest and\nchoiseSt gifts rest upon them through\nout life, is the prayer of their pastor.\nTRESPASS NOTICE.\nThis is to notify all persons not to j\nhunt or trespass in any manner what- j\nsoever upon our lands.\nVernice Berry.\nR. L. Berry. 'j\nDee. 30, 192?.\nNOTICE TO CREDITORS\nIn the District Court of the United\nStates for the Eastern District of\nSouth Carolina.\nIn the 'matter of Watson Fox.\nBatesburg, S. C., Bankrupt.\nNotice is hereby given that the\nabove named bankrupt has filed a\npetition for disabarge and th^t a j\nhearing has been ordered to be\nhad\u201e'before this court at Charleston,!\nS. C., af 11 o\u2019clock in the forenoon, j\non the 30th day of January, A. D. j\n1924, amf that all known creditors\nand other persons in interest may\n\u2022appear at the said tinie and place\n*knd show cause, if any' they have,\nwhy the prajfet of the said petitioner\nshould hot' be granted.\nRICHD. W. HUTSON, Clerk.\nWalter\u2019s Scientifically\nFitted Glasses\nAT PRICES YOU CAN AFFORD\n'f- TO P