the\nJacob J. Bickley lot and dwelling\non Depot street. The house has\nseven rooms, water connection; good\ngarden with some fruit trees. This\nproperty will be sold to the highest\nbidder for cash. Harry A. Roberts,\nAdmr. Est. J. J. Bickley, dead.\n4\nI\nFARMERS MERCHANTS\nBANK COING FORWARD\nThe Farmers and Merchants Bank\nof Leesville is one of the. truly grow\ning institution^ of the county. At\nthe annual meeting, of' the stock-\nholders of the _ bank held on Jan\nuary 3, the officers reported an in\ncrease of 300 per cent, \u2018in deposits\nduring the past year, which is a\nremarkable showing, and the report\nwas received with enthusiasm. The\nbank has also joined the central\nstate banking system proposed iby\nHon. W. W. Bradley, state bank ^ex\naminer, and is the possessor of stpck\ncertificate No. 1.\n\u2022At the meeting1 the following di\nrectors were elected: J. P. Able, J..\nW. Ballentine, 0. C*. Boatwright, Dr.\nJ. H. Burnett, B. F. Caughman, Dr..\nD. M. Crosson, W. M. Epting, J. E.\nR. Kyzer, Willie Long, J. L; B.\n^Oxner, J. Ed. Shealy. The newly\nelected directors then elected the fol\nlowing officers: Dr. D. M. Crosson,\npresident; Dr. J. H. Burnett, \\i&e\npresident; W. E. Moore, cashier; J.\nE. R. Ryker, assistant cashier; J. J.\nAble, assistant cashier. 1\nMrs. Blondell Smith of Gastonia,\n\u2018N. C., is visiting relatives in Lex\nington\nBUILDING SUPPLIES\n7 a\nf' 1\nIN OUR WAREHOUSES AT A8SKM&LT AND TAYLUH\n-i::\nSTREETS, ON SEABOARD AIR LINE TRACKS.\nWe carry a large and complete stock of Agatite Plaster,'Cement.\nPlaster Paris, Metal Lath, Self-centring Lath, Mortar, Stain,- Terra\nCotta Pipe, Flue Lining, Roofing, Pitch, Felt; Paint; Rubber Root\nTV'\nIng. Buldlng Papers, Cement Water Roofing, Cabiot\u2019s Shingle Stain.\nrv v t>'u\nMaoury\u2019s Paints,.-Glass, Russell A Erwin\u2019s Finishing Hardware* a\nOur prices are the best,\u2019'and \"W'e make it a rule to ship order*\n\nsame day received. L\nWe eolcit your orders add Inquirie